text:
East 153rd Street, north side, east from East 157th Street (left) to Cromwell Ave., showing the cleared triangular area bounded by the three aforementioned thoroughfares. On the extreme left is partly visible the Yankee Stadium and, in the background, the Bronx County Court House. The garage is at the S.E. corner of Cromwell Ave. and East 157th Street.

P. L. Sperr.

September 21, 1937.

East 157th Street, at the junction of East 153rd Street. The view is northward.

September 21, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
